description: With the control module output confirmed near 0 V, disconnect the load module. Using the power‑supply module directly, apply 12 V across the load module input terminals (respecting polarity) and measure (1) continuity from the load module positive input terminal to the anode of the series diode and then to the lamp node, and (2) DC voltage at the lamp node and across the diode and lamps when 12 V is applied. This will verify whether the load‑module series diode or its wiring is open/incorrectly referenced, which could be back‑feeding or loading the control module and causing abnormal voltages., outcome='Load Input Cable (+), Main Load lamp, and Internal Indicator Lamp all show nominal continuity values. With 12 V applied, both lamps sit near 0 V on both terminals, while the Load Protection Diode shows about 0.36 V at the anode and ~0 V at the cathode.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=145.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> power supply module output under load (direct to load module),
description: Bypass the control module: disconnect the control module completely and connect the power‑supply module output directly to the load‑module input (ensuring correct polarity). With the battery installed, measure the DC voltage at the load‑module input and observe whether the main lamp and internal indicator lamp illuminate. This tests whether the power‑supply and load modules operate correctly when the control module is removed from the circuit., outcome='Power Supply Module to Load Module continuity tests both report an open circuit with unresolvable probe nodes. With the battery installed, the Load Input Cable (+) measures about 0.36 V relative to ground and the Load Input Cable (−) is near 0 V. Both the Main Load (lamp) and the Internal Indicator Lamp are not lit and show no observable internal faults.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=125.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> power supply module internal series resistance / unintended load between + output and lamp circuit,
description: With the control module still bypassed, keep the PSU connected directly to the load module. Measure DC voltage at three points relative to PSU negative: (1) directly at the battery positive terminal, (2) at the PSU indicator LED anode node, and (3) at the external PSU + output terminal. Then measure current drawn from the battery when the load module is connected vs. disconnected. This will reveal whether an unintended high‑resistance element or parallel path inside the PSU is limiting the output to ~0.36 V under load while still allowing ~12 V at the control‑module input in the original configuration., outcome='Battery measures 12.0 V, and the PSU status LED anode is at about 1.29 V relative to PSU negative. The PSU Output Cable (+) and PSU Output Cable (−) both read ~11.99 V relative to ground, indicating no usable differential output at the PSU terminals. Battery current is 12.362 mA and is unchanged between the load‑connected and load‑disconnected measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=110.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_current', 20.0), ('measure_current', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> power supply module output terminals (floating‑voltage check),
description: With the control and load modules disconnected, measure the DC voltage directly between the PSU Output Cable (+) and PSU Output Cable (−) using the meter’s two probes only on those two terminals (do NOT reference any external ground). Then, still with both other modules disconnected, connect a known good 12 V lamp or a 1 kΩ test resistor directly across the PSU (+) and (−) output cables and again measure the voltage across them. Report (a) the open‑circuit voltage between the PSU outputs and (b) the loaded voltage with the test load attached., outcome='(a) Open‑circuit voltage between PSU Output Cable (+) and PSU Output Cable (−) is approximately 11.99 V.  \n(b) Loaded voltage with the test load attached is also approximately 11.99 V between PSU Output Cable (+) and PSU Output Cable (−).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
